27 SECTION 14. Arkansas Code § 21-4-505 is amended to read as follows:
28 21-4-505. Compensation for unused sick leave of nonclassified employees
29 of state-supported institutions of higher education — Calculation for unused
30 sick leave.
31 (a) At its discretion, a state-supported institution of higher
32 education may compensate a nonclassified an employee of the state-supported
33 institution of higher education for accumulated unused sick leave by
34 providing to the nonclassified employee the same compensation for accumulated
35 unused sick leave provided to a classified employee of the state-supported
36 institution of higher education under § 21-4-501.
8 03/10/2025 2:56:07 PM CRH246

SB417
1 (b) Compensation for accumulated unused sick leave under this section
2 shall not be used by the Arkansas Public Employees' Retirement System in the
3 calculation of final average compensation under § 24-4-101.
4 (c) Unused sick leave for nonclassified employees of state-supported
5 institutions of higher education shall accrue at the same rate as unused sick
6 leave accrues under § 21-4-207 for classified employees for calculations made
